Pauline Bonaparte ( 20 October 1780 – 9 June 1825 ) was an Italian noblewoman , the first sovereign Duchess of Guastalla in Italy , an imperial French Princess and the Princess consort of Sulmona and Rossano .
She was the sixth child of Letizia Ramolino and Carlo Buonaparte , Corsica 's representative to the court of King Louis XVI of France .
Her elder brother , Napoleon , was the first Emperor of the French .
She married Charles Leclerc , a French general , a union ended by his death in 1802 .
Later , she married Camillo Borghese , 6th Prince of Sulmona .
Her only child , Dermide Leclerc , born from her first marriage , died in childhood .
She was the only Bonaparte sibling to visit Napoleon in exile on his principality , Elba .
